review:
Recommended with a few reservations:

- it's very short, the above 3.3 hours on record included full replay of 3rd chapter for some achievements. You can be done under 2 hours doing all the "exploring" at your own pace;

-it's not point-and-click adventure per se, meaning there isn' t much "adventuring".It has some elements of it (you get to use inventory several times throughout the game), but it's mostly very linear dialogue-heavy story where you do what you're told by the narrative;

-I wouldn't call it "horror" either. It's more of a psychological drama with some strange happenings, it has a dark, gloomy feel over it, but it's not terrifying, spooky or chilling...more so thought-provoking and just makes you ponder

Now with that being said, the story is intriguing, (if somewhat bizarre); there is a good quality voice-acting and the game turned out to be pretty atmospheric. It will be a decent hold-over for people who got to know "The Cat Lady" and subsequent "Downfall" and now roaming the universe in search of something that can fill the void :)
It isn't close to those games at either depth, quality or atmosphere, and yet I feel like the fans of those would appreciate a short forray into the genre.
